# Raspberry Pi Set Up

1. Get the Raspberry Pi OS (64-bit)

```bash
sudo raspi-config
# Interface Options → enable Camera
# Interface Options → enable I2C
# System Options → set locale/timezone
sudo reboot
```

3. make sure you have python updated with the libaries we will likely use

```bash
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y python3-pip python3-venv python3-opencv \
    libatlas-base-dev libjpeg-dev libtiff5 libopenjp2-7 \
    i2c-tools git
```

'pip install opencv-python-headless' if 'python-opencv' doesn't work

---

